These beautiful Italian Renaissance drawings, lent to us by the Cabinet des Dessins of the MusÃƒÂ©e du Louvre, come as the latest wave of French generosity to The Metropolitan. They follow upon the glorious tapestries lent to us earlier this year for the exhibition Masterpieces of Tapestry from the Fourteenth to the Sixteenth Century. Loan exhibition of such great works of art are the first positive results of recent agreements between the National Museums of France and the Metropolitan intended to facilitate the exchange of works of art and of personnel between France and America.

In October, 1973, the Metropolitan sent to Paris and exhibition that included its finest drawings by French artists of the nineteenth century; the present splendid selection of drawings by Italian Renaissance masters from the Louvre is France's response to New York's loan to Paris.
